Commodity names have been adjusted to align with the Variant of North American Product Classification System (NAPCS) Canada 2017 Version 2.0 - Agricultural goods. These commodities include fresh and processed fruits.
Cultivated area includes bearing and non-bearing area.
Prior to 2018, fresh blackberries, fresh currants and fresh haskaps were included in the other fresh fruits category.   As of 2018 they are published in their own categories in this table.

Conversion factors used for 1 bushel of apples from 1926 to 1964 equals 45.0 pounds, 1965 equals 44.5 pounds, 1966 equals 44.0 pounds, 1967 equals 43.5 pounds, 1968 equals 43.0 pounds, 1969 equals 42.5 pounds, from 1970 on equals 42.0 pounds.
The value of the crop from 1984 onward is not comparable to previous years because of a change in reporting techniques for New Brunswick only.

Prior to 1987, total production includes figures from on-farm land and unmanaged Crown land. As of 1987, only on-farm production and value are available. Unmanaged Crown land is excluded beginning in 1987.
Fresh blueberries includes fresh lowbush blueberries and fresh highbush blueberries.
Fresh grapes includes fresh Labrusca grapes and fresh vinifera, fresh French hybrid grapes.
As of April 27, 1983, revisions back to 1926 in British Columbia were carried out to reflect that 1 quart equals 1.25 pounds.
“Total fresh fruits” is equivalent to the sum of all North American Product Classification System variant codes found in this table.
